## Conventions

- Each memory file has frontmatter: `name` · `description` · `type`.
- Update or remove memories that turn out wrong (do not stack contradictions).
- Memories ARE NOT for: code patterns, file paths, conventions (read the code), git history, ephemeral task state.
- Before recommending from memory: verify the file/function/flag still exists. Memory is frozen-in-time.
- Read this file before any session-start action; let memories guide tone, depth, and approach.
